<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7364> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7364" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Named in an inscription of Concordia, which, though possibly Augustan, probably dates from the Late Republic (Pais, Suppl. To CIL 5, no. 411; cf. Niccolini, FTP p. 505; F. Broilo, Iscr. Lap. Lat. Mus. Naz. Concordiese 2, 1984, no. 90). Perhaps a relative of Pilia, wife of Atticus. See the full discussion by Geza Alföldy in Aquileia Nostra 51, 1980, 257-264.[156x]" ;
	dprr:hasID 7364 .
